<item>
            <title>[SPARK-8458] ORC data source can only write to the file system defined in Hadoop configuration</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-8458</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;To reproduce this issue, we first define &lt;tt&gt;fs.default.name&lt;/tt&gt; in Hadoop &lt;tt&gt;core-site.xml&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&amp;lt;configuration&amp;gt;
    ...
    &amp;lt;property&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;fs.default.name&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;hdfs://localhost:9000&amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;
    ...
&amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then execute the following Spark shell snippet:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;sqlContext.range(0, 10).coalesce(1).write.mode(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;overwrite&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).format(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;orc&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).save(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;file:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;///tmp/foo&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The write job succeeds, but you can only find &lt;tt&gt;_SUCCESS&lt;/tt&gt; under &lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;file:///tmp/foo&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;file:///tmp/foo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;. Data files are actually written to HDFS directory &lt;tt&gt;/tmp/foo/_temporary&lt;/tt&gt; and left uncommitted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason is that, &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/9b2002722273f98e193ad6cd54c9626292ab27d1/sql/hive/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/hive/orc/OrcRelation.scala#L113&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;this line&lt;/a&gt; uses &lt;tt&gt;Path.toUri.getPath&lt;/tt&gt; rather than &lt;tt&gt;Path.toString&lt;/tt&gt; to pass the path string to &lt;tt&gt;OrcRecordWriter&lt;/tt&gt; constructor, and this essentially strips the scheme part of the path.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
